-- Thorning-Schmidt Says EU to Aim for Growth, Newsletter Reports
-- B y   R e b e c c a   C h r i s t i e
-- 2012-06-25T14:34:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/thorning-schmidt-says-eu-to-aim-for-growth-newsletter-reports.html
European Union leaders aim to agree
this week on new ways to boost growth, including a capital
increase for the  European Investment Bank , when they meet in
Brussels June 28-29, a newsletter cited Danish Prime Minster
Helle Thorning-Schmidt as saying.  “We will have a heavy agenda for the meeting” the
Confederation of Danish Industry cited Thorning-Schmidt as
saying in the newsletter published today. “We will work to
reach agreement on a compact for growth and jobs with
initiatives both on national and EU level which will help get
Europe back on a track.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Rebecca Christie  in Brussels at 
 rchristie4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
